==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: carcinoid
<hw>carcinoid</hw> <ety>[From Gr. <grk>karki`nos</grk>, a crab +
<ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small tumor (benign or
malignant) arising from the mucosa of the gastrointestinal tract; it is
usually associated with excessive secretion of serotonin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carcinological</ent>⟦br⟧
